      "content": "I hear the deep despair in your words, and it's clear that the pain you're carrying right now is overwhelming and feels impossible to escape. When grief hits that hard, it can make the world feel empty and the future feel pointless, which makes it incredibly difficult to see any other way forward.\n\nPlease know that your feelings are valid, but the idea that there is no way out of this pain is a common part of the grieving process, not a reflection of reality. Sometimes, when the mind is this exhausted, it suggests that the pain is too great to bear, but it doesn't mean it has to be permanent.\n\nIf you feel like you cannot survive another day or that the weight of this is too much to carry alone, please consider reaching out to someone who can offer immediate support. In the US, you can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, which provides free, confidential, 24/7 support. If you are outside the US, please look for local crisis lines or emergency services in your area. You don't have to go through this alone.",
